description: The Adidas Ivy Park x Adidas Ultra Boost OG 'Halls of Ivy' is a special edition running shoe that features a monochrome neon green colorway. The shoe is made with a flexible Primeknit upper, molded midfoot cage, and external heel counter, and includes dual Adidas and Ivy Park branding on the sockliner. The sneaker sits atop a full-length Boost midsole, reinforced underfoot by a Stretchweb Continental rubber outsole. This shoe is perfect for athletes or anyone who wants to add a touch of style to their workout gear.

The Blondey McCoy x adidas Gazelle Indoor is nowhere near as revealing as the above-mentioned Shell Toe. In place of the translucent TPU, the pair proffers an off-white ripstop, which builds out both the base as well as the tongue. Black, then, details many of the adjacent fixtures, from the resculpted midsole to the glossy overlays layered along the toe, eye stays, and heel tab. description:
The adidas Forum first stepped onto the hardwood back in '84, bursting onto the scene in a flurry of expression. While they're no longer for basketball, they are still always down to make an impression. And this pair does — with the same X detail and ankle strap that solidified their place as an icon. A clear tribute to the '70s and '80s, they have a faded vibe done in soft, mellow colors.
